    "name": "Absolute hemolysis prediction requirement for Class III VAD",
    "description": "The CFD model shall predict absolute normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values within 10% of experimentally measured values across all 5 specified operating conditions. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification shall demonstrate 95% prediction intervals within ±15% of mean predicted NIH. Model Risk Level 5 credibility requirements shall be satisfied for all 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors prior to regulatory submission.",
    "requirementSource": "FDA 510(k) submission requirements for Class III ventricular assist devices; ASME V&V 40-2018 Section 6"
  },
